`,"The RegionSplitter tool is provided with HBase, and uses a ",e.jsx(i.em,{children:"SplitAlgorithm"})," to determine split points for you. As parameters, you give it the algorithm, desired number of regions, and column families. It includes three split algorithms. The first is the ",e.jsx(i.a,{href:"https://hbase.apache.org/devapidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/util/RegionSplitter.HexStringSplit.html",children:e.jsx(i.code,{children:"HexStringSplit"})})," algorithm, which assumes the row keys are hexadecimal strings. The second is the ",e.jsx(i.a,{href:"https://hbase.apache.org/devapidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/util/RegionSplitter.DecimalStringSplit.html",children:e.jsx(i.code,{children:"DecimalStringSplit"})})," algorithm, which assumes the row keys are decimal strings in the range 00000000 to 99999999. The third, ",e.jsx(i.a,{href:"https://hbase.apache.org/devapidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/util/RegionSplitter.UniformSplit.html",children:e.jsx(i.code,{children:"UniformSplit"})}),", assumes the row keys are random byte arrays. You will probably need to develop your own ",e.jsx(i.a,{href:"https://hbase.apache.org/devapidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/util/RegionSplitter.SplitAlgorithm.html",children:e.jsx(i.code,{children:"SplitAlgorithm"})}),", using the provided ones as models."]}),`
