`,e.jsxs(i.p,{children:["Both Master and RegionServer participate in the event of online region merges. Client sends merge RPC to the master, then the master moves the regions together to the RegionServer where the more heavily loaded region resided. Finally the master sends the merge request to this RegionServer which then runs the merge. Similar to process of region splitting, region merges run as a local transaction on the RegionServer. It offlines the regions and then merges two regions on the file system, atomically delete merging regions from ",e.jsx(i.code,{children:"hbase:meta"})," and adds the merged region to ",e.jsx(i.code,{children:"hbase:meta"}),", opens the merged region on the RegionServer and reports the merge to the Master."]}),`
